continues to affect the market for non-bulk, time-sensitive freight. The potential expansion of longer combination vehicles could
further encroach upon markets traditionally served by railroads. In order to remain competitive, BNSF Railway and other railroads
seek to develop and implement operating efficiencies to improve productivity.
As railroads streamline, rationalize and otherwise enhance their franchises, competition among rail carriers intensifies. BNSF
Railway’s primary rail competitor in the Western region of the United States is the Union Pacific Railroad Company. Other Class I
